ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken:
What is your overall assessment of this course?
What is your overall rating of the primary instructor?
The primary instructor's sensitivity to students and ability to provide students with adequate feedback was:

narratives.question_text: Indicate the total number of hours per week (outside the classroom) you spent on this course:
Looking back on this course, what is your overall assessment of the course:  What are its strengths and weaknesses, and in what ways might it be improved?
comments: It's a good course that introduces you to a variety of research that is currently going on in the field. Great for those that will be doing their prospectuses next year.
The seminars were hard to follow as a first year MPH Biostatistics student. I think it would be more appropriate to ask Biostatistics students to take it 2nd year.

narratives.question_text: Please evaluate the instructor of this course. What are the instructor's strengths and weaknesses, and in what ways might his or her teaching be improved?
How would you summarize this course for a fellow student? Would you recommend it to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a great course to meet new professor's and see their research. Being that it's only a seminar, it doesn't change your course load that much but might give the necessary idea for your thesis.
